{
  "texts": [
    "D-NeRF (Pumarola et al. 2021) models the deformation field Φ(x, t) → ∆x where ∆x is the predicted positional change of a ray-sample relative to a canonical static field Φ(x + ∆x, t) → (c, σ).",
    "Relative to global space, this learns an SE(3) transformation.",
    "Learning a canonical static space is a robust way of ensuring volumetric consistency with time.",
    "Though intuitive, this lends itself to issues when a scene is not continuously in-frame.",
    "To counterbalance this, methods such as K-Planes decompose static and dynamic volumes representations."
  ]
}